"I've always second-guessed my writing, and I think that this was the recognition that I needed especially the fact that I was judged by my peers, and editors and professors," said Marchelle. The RDMAs recognise journalists and media at large for their efforts to positively influence perceptions and habits related to the irresponsible use of alcohol. The awards ceremony was hosted on last week on Thursday night at an awards ceremony held at Four Seasons Westcliff Hotel in Johannesburg. The winners were selected by a panel of judges made up of media experts and announced on Thursday night. Independent Media was amongst the top three nominated for Media House of the Year. Read full article>> https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/gauteng/iol-lifestyle-journalist-scoops-two-diageo-rdma-awards-34030172.